British Prime Minister Boris Johnson said on Saturday that English Premier League matches will continue during a month-long national lockdown starting next week. The return of the lockdown was to contain the coronavirus outbreak. Johnson had in an address said there was a need for a return to the lockdown measure as the pandemic was showing no signs of abating. (Reuters/NAN) READ ALSO: Burna Boy releases new single to honour victims of Lekki shooting Nigeria’s importation from China hits N1.26trn in Q2 – NBS